<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>The United Nations Commission for India and Pakistan was composed of
                                the following members: <list>
                                    <item>Czechoslovakia—nominated by India, February 10.</item>
                                    <item>Belgium—appointed by the Council, April 23.</item>
                                    <item>Colombia—appointed by the Council, April 23.</item>
                                    <pb facs="0354" n="340" xml:id="pg_340"/>
                                    <item>Argentina—nominated by Pakistan, April 30.</item>
                                    <item>United States—designated by the President of the Council,
                                        May 7, in the absence of agreement between Argentina and
                                        Czechoslovakia on the member to be designated by
                                        them.</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>